---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-8 px-6 py-12">
    <section>
        <h2 class="mb-4 mt-8 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
            Get Involved
        </h2>

        <h3 class="mb-3 mt-6 text-2xl font-semibold">Volunteer</h3>

        <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-7">
            We are always looking for more volunteers to knock on doors and hand
            out flyers! If you’re interested in contributing to the campaign,
            click the button below:
        </p>

        <a
            href="https://forms.gle/CEt3uF6JWa6MPTFH6"
            target="_blank"
            class="font-semibold text-blue-600 underline underline-offset-2 transition-colors hover:text-blue-800"
        >
            Volunteer Form
        </a>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3 class="mb-3 mt-6 text-2xl font-semibold">Donations</h3>

        <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-7">
            My campaign will be <b class="font-bold">completely self-funded</b>.
            I will not be accepting donations, except from direct family members
            up to the maximum contribution limit for individuals.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-7">
            <b class="font-bold">I don’t believe money belongs in politics</b>,
            especially at the local level.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3 class="mb-3 mt-6 text-2xl font-semibold">Lawn Signs</h3>

        <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-7">I won’t be providing lawn signs.</p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-7">
            It’s a <b class="font-bold">waste of money</b> and they are
            <b class="font-bold"> bad for the environment</b>. In Sydenham
            District, we also have many multi-residential properties, so it can
            get messy if residents want to display signs for different
            candidates on the same lawn.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-7">
            I reached out to the other Sydenham District candidates and
            suggested that we agree to a “<b class="font-bold">No Lawn Sign</b>”
            campaign. As an alternative, I have suggested that we could create
            <b class="font-bold"> 8.5” x 11” paper signs</b> (fully recyclable) that
            residents could tape to their doors or display in their windows to show
            support for their preferred candidate.
        </p>

        <!-- <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-7">
            If you want one of my printable 8.5” x 11” signs for your window or
            door, <a
                href="#"
                class="text-blue-600 underline underline-offset-2 transition-colors hover:text-blue-800"
            >
                click here
            </a>.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-7">
            As of July xx 2026, there is no consensus on this issue yet. Please
            check back here for updates.
        </p> -->
    </section>
</div>
